# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AuraTalk backend — environment overrides for `docker compose`.
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in real values for production.
# If you leave this empty, compose falls back to local MinIO dev defaults.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Media object storage (S3-compatible) ──
# LOCAL DEV (default, no .env needed): MinIO at http://minio:9000
#
# PRODUCTION — Backblaze B2:
#   1. B2 console → create an Application Key scoped to your bucket.
#   2. Use the *bucket NAME* (not the bucket ID) for S3_BUCKET.
#   3. B2 supports virtual-host style, so keep S3_FORCE_PATH_STYLE=false.
#
# S3_ENDPOINT=https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com
# S3_REGION=us-east-005
# S3_BUCKET=your-bucket-name
# S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-b2-application-key-id
# S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-b2-application-key
# S3_FORCE_PATH_STYLE=false

# Max encrypted blob size accepted by the upload endpoint (bytes). Default 25 MiB.
# MEDIA_MAX_BYTES=26214400
